			<ns0:name>mcgra...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/109286297231979736865/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">There is only 128MB between the canonical user rodata address and the IRT rodata address.  Since newlib's malloc only uses sbrk, this leaves something less than 128MB of malloc space available in newlib-based nexes built to run in the browser.

Reproduce with:

./scons --mode=dbg-host,nacl,nacl_irt_test run_bigalloc_test_irt
